    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains 12 monthly observations of retail sales (univariate time series). Synthetic data was generated with \u03bc=130.4K and \u03c3=48.2K, simulating seasonal patterns with summer peak (Jun: 203K) and winter trough (Dec: 63K). The 3D column chart emphasizes monthly comparisons while maintaining value readability through front-facing data labels. Though 3D effects increase chart ink, controlled alpha/beta angles (15\u00b0) preserve value perception per Cairo's principles of visual integrity. The blue color gradient and dollar-formatted labels follow financial visualization conventions, while the suppressed legend reduces cognitive load for single-series data. Statistical anchors: Synthetic data shows 66% variance reduction from peak to trough, with Q2 sales averaging 166K vs Q4 average of 92K."
